File Transfer and Remote Command Protocol
This project focuses on the design and implementation of a custom TCP-based protocol for remote server interaction. The system facilitates the secure uploading and downloading of files and allows for the execution of fundamental Linux CLI commands from a client.

Technical Stack & Core Concepts
Language: C
Networking: UNIX Network Programming, TCP/IP
System Programming: Multi-threading, Signals, Linux System-Level Concepts
Data Structures: Custom data structures optimized for protocol handling

Platform: Fedora Linux
